==German==
===Etymology===
Essentially a joke: in the local dialect, ''Kann isch ne halve han?'' means "Can i get a half one (sandwich)". Foreigners interpreted this as ''Halve Hahn'', "half a rooster". Nowadays, it's often written like this on the menu of rustical restaurants in Cologne.

===Noun===
'''Halve Hahn''' ''m''
# (Cologne dialect) a [[cheese]] [[sandwich]], cut in half.